> <OLD>
>
> At this point, as the group came on to a seeming battle sight, DINOBOT held
> up then as the MAXIMALS took the forefront.  Tracking was not his forte, and
> for now he would remain mostly quiet.  HE was along for muscle, after all.
>
> Whereas VICE GRIP was an expert tracker of some ability, for the moment he
> was not visible (and eprhaps unknown) just digging along over underground.
> Along with DRILL BIT, a few dozen meters and tracking the TRANSFORMERS up
> above by their IFF signals through the dirt, going past heavy roots and
> vines underneath.
>
> And WASPINATOR, flying along in the air, went very, very slowly.  While he
> was an agile and adept flier, the increasing undergrowth made him slow down
> heavily to avoid being bludgeoned.
>
> And so, as they found tracks, DINOBOT watched as the battle sight was
> analyzed by the MAXIMALS, waiting for further instructions.

"Well what have you got?" INJECTOR, one of the FUZOR's said as he came
walking up, his right hand, more of a stinger than hand, using it to
brush his way through the underbrush.

TERRORGATOR glanced over at him irritably, "We have a second path."

"What is it, or who is it?" SKYSHADOW said in a silky smooth, and yet
still somehow dangerous voice as he walked up, causing both INJECTOR
and TERORGATOR to straighten respectfully, or perhaps fearfully.

CRYOTEK pulled out a small scanner and oriented it on the trail of the
second path, "Curious. It is the lubricant from a sweep, several of
them."

(TAG)

Preston
